---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/sections/Section.astro';
import CTABanner from '../../components/sections/CTABanner.astro';
import Card from '../../components/ui/Card.astro';
import Button from '../../components/ui/Button.astro';
import ScrollReveal from '../../components/animation/ScrollReveal.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Deeper Understanding | IBC Academy"
  description="You know what IBC is. Now understand why it works. Austrian economics, policy mechanics, and the toughest questions — answered honestly."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <Section background="cream">
    <ScrollReveal direction="up">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <span class="hero-eyebrow">For Those Who Want to Go Deeper</span>
        <h1 class="hero-title">You Know What IBC Is. <br />Now Understand Why It Works.</h1>
        <p class="hero-text">
          You've read the overview. You understand the basic premise — use a whole life policy as a personal banking system. Maybe you've even read <em>Becoming Your Own Banker</em> once.
        </p>
        <p class="hero-text">
          But something isn't clicking yet. You can explain the concept to someone else, but you can't quite explain <em>why</em> it's inevitable. You want the foundations, not the summary.
        </p>
        <p class="hero-text">
          This path is built for you. Six articles that go from economic theory to policy mechanics to the hardest questions critics raise — and answer all of them honestly. No hand-waving. No "just trust the process."
        </p>
      </div>
    </ScrollReveal>
  </Section>

  <!-- What This Is (And Isn't) -->
  <Section title="What This Journey Is (And Isn't)">
    <ScrollReveal direction="up">
      <div class="clarity-content">
        <div class="clarity-grid">
          <div class="clarity-box">
            <h3 class="clarity-heading is-not">This is NOT:</h3>
            <ul class="clarity-list">
              <li>A rehash of the basics you already know</li>
              <li>Hype dressed up in bigger words</li>
              <li>A pitch disguised as education</li>
              <li>Hand-waving past the hard questions</li>
              <li>Content that avoids the tradeoffs</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="clarity-box">
            <h3 class="clarity-heading is-yes">This IS:</h3>
            <ul class="clarity-list">
              <li>The Austrian economics behind the concept</li>
              <li>Policy mechanics explained without shortcuts</li>
              <li>Every tough objection addressed head-on</li>
              <li>The path from understanding to conviction</li>
              <li>Depth that respects your intelligence</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="clarity-footer">
          By the end, you'll either have the "lightbulb moment" that makes IBC feel inevitable — or you'll have the clearest possible reasons for your skepticism. Either way, you'll understand this at a level most practitioners don't.
        </p>
      </div>
    </ScrollReveal>
  </Section>

  <!-- The 6 Articles -->
  <Section title="Your 6-Article Journey" subtitle="Each article takes 8–12 minutes. Expect economics, mechanics, and honesty — not talking points." background="cream">
    <div class="journey-grid">
      <ScrollReveal direction="up" delay={0}>
        <a href="/learn/articles/deeper-01-economics-behind" class="journey-card-link">
          <div class="journey-card">
            <span class="journey-number">01</span>
            <h3 class="journey-title">Why IBC Works: The Economics Behind the Concept</h3>
            <p class="journey-desc">Nelson Nash didn't invent IBC in a vacuum. He stood on the shoulders of Menger, Mises, and the Austrian school. Here's the economic foundation that makes IBC inevitable.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal direction="up" delay={100}>
        <a href="/learn/articles/deeper-02-five-human-problems" class="journey-card-link">
          <div class="journey-card">
            <span class="journey-number">02</span>
            <h3 class="journey-title">The Five Human Problems IBC Solves</h3>
            <p class="journey-desc">Nash identified five problems every human faces with money. Understanding these problems is the key to understanding why the solution works.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal direction="up" delay={200}>
        <a href="/learn/articles/deeper-03-how-policy-works" class="journey-card-link">
          <div class="journey-card">
            <span class="journey-number">03</span>
            <h3 class="journey-title">How a Whole Life Policy Actually Works</h3>
            <p class="journey-desc">Base premium. Paid-up additions. Cash value. Dividends. Non-direct recognition. Here's what's actually happening inside your policy — no hand-waving.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal direction="up" delay={300}>
        <a href="/learn/articles/deeper-04-policy-loans" class="journey-card-link">
          <div class="journey-card">
            <span class="journey-number">04</span>
            <h3 class="journey-title">Policy Loans: The Mechanism That Changes Everything</h3>
            <p class="journey-desc">This is where most people's understanding breaks down. Policy loans aren't what you think — and that's exactly why they work.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal direction="up" delay={400}>
        <a href="/learn/articles/deeper-05-toughest-questions" class="journey-card-link">
          <div class="journey-card">
            <span class="journey-number">05</span>
            <h3 class="journey-title">The Toughest Questions About IBC (Answered Honestly)</h3>
            <p class="journey-desc">MEC limits. Opportunity cost. "It takes too long." "I can do better in the market." Every hard question, addressed head-on.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal direction="up" delay={500}>
        <a href="/learn/articles/deeper-06-lightbulb-moment" class="journey-card-link">
          <div class="journey-card">
            <span class="journey-number">06</span>
            <h3 class="journey-title">The Lightbulb Moment</h3>
            <p class="journey-desc">Some people get it on the first read. Others take months. Both are fine. Here's what the moment of clarity actually feels like — and how to find yours.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Why This Matters -->
  <Section title="Why Go Deeper?">
    <ScrollReveal direction="up">
      <div class="why-content">
        <p class="why-text">
          Most people learn IBC like a product. They memorize the steps — fund a policy, take a loan, pay it back. That's fine for getting started.
        </p>
        <blockquote class="why-quote">
          "The problem with trying to teach a process without teaching the underlying economics is that the student never develops conviction. And without conviction, they quit."
        </blockquote>
        <p class="why-attribution">— Nelson Nash, paraphrased from Becoming Your Own Banker</p>
        <p class="why-text">
          Nash spent years studying Austrian economics before he ever connected it to whole life insurance. He didn't start with the product. He started with the problem.
        </p>
        <p class="why-text">
          That's what this path gives you. Not a better sales pitch — a real foundation. The kind that turns "I think this makes sense" into "I see why this is mathematically and economically inevitable."
        </p>
        <p class="why-text">
          The lightbulb moment is real. And it's worth pursuing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </ScrollReveal>
  </Section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <Section background="cream">
    <ScrollReveal direction="up">
      <div class="cta-content">
        <h2 class="cta-title">Start With the Economics</h2>
        <p class="cta-text">
          Article 1 begins where Nash began — with Menger, Mises, and the Austrian understanding of money. Everything else builds from there.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-button">
          <Button variant="primary" size="lg" href="/learn/articles/deeper-01-economics-behind">
            Begin Article 1 →
          </Button>
        </div>
        <p class="cta-note">
          Already past the economics? Jump to any article above. They're designed to be read in order, but each stands on its own.
        </p>
      </div>
    </ScrollReveal>
  </Section>

  <!-- Final Note -->
  <CTABanner
    heading="Want to Discuss What You're Learning?"
    description="Join 500+ people studying IBC seriously. Ask the hard questions. Get real answers from practitioners, not salespeople."
    buttonText="Join the Community"
    buttonHref="https://skool.com/ibc-academy"
  />
</PageLayout>

<style>
  /* Hero Section */
  .hero-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-gold, #C9A962);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--color-navy, #1B2A4A);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .hero-title {
      font-size: 3rem;
    }
  }

  .hero-text {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .hero-text:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Clarity Section */
  .clarity-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .clarity-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .clarity-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .clarity-box {
    background: var(--color-cream, #FAF9F6);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .clarity-heading {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .clarity-heading.is-not {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
  }

  .clarity-heading.is-yes {
    color: var(--color-navy, #1B2A4A);
  }

  .clarity-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .clarity-list li {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .clarity-list li::before {
    content: "•";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-gold, #C9A962);
  }

  .clarity-footer {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    text-align: center;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Journey Section */
  .journey-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .journey-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .journey-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .journey-card-link {
    text-decoration: none;
    display: block;
  }

  .journey-card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(27, 42, 74, 0.08);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
  }

  .journey-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(27, 42, 74, 0.12);
  }

  .journey-number {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-gold, #C9A962);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .journey-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-navy, #1B2A4A);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
  }

  .journey-desc {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Why Section */
  .why-content {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .why-text {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem 0;
  }

  .why-quote {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--color-navy, #1B2A4A);
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem 0;
    padding: 0 1rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-gold, #C9A962);
    text-align: left;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .why-quote {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
      padding: 0 2rem;
    }
  }

  .why-attribution {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
    text-align: left;
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .why-attribution {
      padding-left: 2rem;
    }
  }

  /* CTA Section */
  .cta-content {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--color-navy, #1B2A4A);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .cta-text {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
  }

  .cta-button {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cta-note {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
